  <notes>
  This was the big experiment with mash hopping and first wort
  hopping.  Our conclusion was that FWH was useful from at least
  a convenience point of view and that mash hopping didn't work
  for us at all.  There is *no* saaz character to this beer.
  For all that, it's a nice beer.  One or two of the bottles got
  infected.  The yeast is all wrong for this beer, and the hops
  don't come out at all.  I wouldn't do this one again.  BTW, notice
  that our subsequent repitchings of 1098 are resulting in higher
  attenuation.
